{
	"name": "Arcane of Flames",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/magic/fire/beam-jet-stream-spiral-yellow.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Fire is the elemental power of destruction, a power every user of the arcane uses this ancestral art to destroy their foes. You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>Your Charisma score increases by 1.</p></li><li><p>You add the <em>fire</em> school of spells to your spell list, and you take two spells from this list for a level you can cast. You can cast one of these spells once per Long Rest without expending a spell slot, and they are considered always prepared and don’t count toward the number of spells you may know.</p></li><li><p>When you cast a spell that deals fire damage, you can add your Charisma modifier to one damage roll of the spell. You can do this a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per Short Rest.</p></li></ul>",
